(5, 5, 'ws 5.pdf', 'ws_page_05.jpg', 'South Africans are hurting because the destruction of our heritage, the killing of our rhinos, hasnt abated despite many outstanding efforts. The situation is not the sole responsibility of government, or conservation agencies. Every individual in this generation will be responsible if the rhino become extinct because it has started during our time.Hundreds of thousands of people want their voice to be heard. You may be one of them.  Roots, a top advertising agency who designed the advert on the opposite page, have created a channel. They give their rationale and announce the viral campaign in this edition. Some good news is the positive results of a unique aerial support project in KwaZulu-Natal also in this edition. For it to continue, Vol 12 No 1 of 4 2012Autumn EditionEDITORRod MacLeod  Cell: 082 782 3150 E-mail:rod@wildsidesa.co.zaMANAGING EDITORJennifer Crawford  Cell: 082 329 1739 E-mail: editor@wildsidesa.co.za EDITORIALRod visited Princes Grant and Woodlands Lodge to capture the images as well as applied his professional photographers eye to numerous other spreads in Wild-side. Rod is also the creative force behind the design.PerspectiveJennifer CrawfordJennifer looks after the content of Wildside and for this edition was privileged to interview Dr Ian Player and Lawrence Anthony. Jennifer could not pass up an escape to a wonderful destination, namely Springbok Lodge.Mark AddisonMark brought diving with wild tiger sharks to the world. A passionate conserva-tionist, hes spent 20 years pioneering shark diving in southern Africa. He contrib-utes to scientific studies and heads an underwater filming company. Lisa KohlerLisa went to Princes Grant and, as always, she managed to find the less than obvi-Fiona AyerstSharks hold a special fascination for Fiona, one of Africas best known and experi-enced SCUBA divers and underwater photographers. Shes interacted with sharks throughout her 25 years of diving and writes two articles for this edition.Micah van Schalkwyk and Sheelagh AntrobusSheelagh heads up the African Conservation Trust and Micah works with her. These rhino warriors recently spent time with an anti-poaching team and their article sheds light on some of the issues.Tony CarnieTony looks at rhino killings by bogus sport hunters from China, Thailand and Jessica MoyaJessica is studying Advanced Professional Photography at Vega and is seldom seen without her camera. Jessica took the photographs of Miss Earth for this edition bringing a youthful energy into the spread.WILDSIDE SUPPORTS MEDIA FREEDOM AUTUMN 2012 ILDSIDEHelp stop the bloody carnage and become a  &#x0088;&#x008f;`&#x0088;`i>&#x0088;&#x009c;&#x009c;&#x009c;WWW.WILDSIDESA.CO.ZA ILDSIDEBurchells coucal (Centropus burchellii'),
