(10, 10, 'ws 10.pdf', 'ws_page_10.jpg', ' SUMMEISANDLWANA  LODGE 4HYJOZSV^S`H[[HJRH[KH^Uand eat up the red soldiers, Cetshwayo, King of the Zulu 5H[PVU 0[PZ^P[O[OLZLspine-tingling words in mind that Isandlwana Lodge invites NLZ[Z[VL_WLYPLUJLP[Zunique hospitality in authentic surroundings and to listen to the fascinating stories of the Anglo Zulu War.  Isandlwana Lodge is located in the area of KwaZulu-Natal renowned for its natural beauty and formidable battle scars. The thought-provoking, four-star lodge is literally carved into the side of the Nyoni rockface, just below where the Zulu commander, Ntshingwaya Ka Manhole Khosa, stood during the epic historical battle as he watched the mighty Zulu impis overcome the British troops under the command of Lord Chelmsford at the base of Isandlwana Mountain on 22nd of January 1879.Designed to complement the aesthetics of the natural environment, the lodge looks as if it grew out of the rocks upon which it is built. The property has 12 stylish bedrooms, each en-suite, with a private balcony overlooking the panorama of [OLIH[[SLLSK;OLYLPZHSZVa guesthouse with three twin rooms which is equipped for self-catering purposes. Guests from around the world remain mesmerised by the lore surrounding Isandlwana. Vivid stories of the battle at Isandlwana and the attack on the garrison at Rorkes Drift are told by resident historian, author and Fellow of the Royal Geographical Society, Rob Gerrard, or one of his associates.  You are sure to have an  Special holiday rates from R1120.00 pppns including meals. 034 271 8201/4/5 lodge@isandlwana.co.zaNAMBITI PLAINS PRIVATE GAME LODGE 5HTIP[P7SHPUZ7YP]H[L.HTL3VKNLHZ[HY(MYPJHU3\\_Y`Eco Lodge, lies nestled within the smoldering beauty of a picturesque landscape VM[OLZWLJ[HJSHY5HTIP[P.HTL9LZLY]LHWYP]H[LBig 5 bush retreat and game conservancy set on 20 000 acres of malaria-free bushveld PU2^HAS5H[HSZYYVUKLKI`[OL)H[[SLLSKZThe abundance of natural water, perennial rivers and beautiful waterfalls on t