(41, 'yes', 'No', 'Advertise', 5, 'Rod MacLeod', 'About the Magazine for Advertisers', '', '', '', '', '<p>Wildside Magazine brings you the best in Ecotravel, Outdoor Adventure and Conservation in Africa. Please see below a comprehensive outline of Wildside''s Editorial focus, Readership, Distribution, and the Rate Card information.</p>\r\n<ul class="nav nav-tabs"><li><a href="#Wildside" data-toggle="tab">The Mag</a></li><li><a href="#Readers" data-toggle="tab">Our Readers</a></li><li><a href="#Facts" data-toggle="tab">Fast Facts</a></li><li><a href="#Rate" data-toggle="tab">Rate Card</a></li><li><a href="#Distribution" data-toggle="tab">Distribution</a></li><li><a href="#Booking" data-toggle="tab">Booking Deadlines</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div class="tab-content">\r\n\r\n<div class="tab-pane active" id="Wildside">\r\n<a href="http://issuu.com/wildside/docs/wildside_magazine_summer_2010?mode=embed&amp;layout=http%3A%2F%2Fskin.issuu.com%2Fv%2Flight%2Flayout.xml&amp;showFlipBtn=true"><img src="http://www.wildsidesa.co.za/admin/upload/server/php/files/cover.jpg" width="254" height="343" class="image" /></a></td>\r\n<td valign="top"> <h2>Wildside is a quality, exciting, quarterly magazine about ecotravel, adventure and conservation. Its editorial focus stretches from Cape Town to Zanzibar. Special focus is given to the eastern seaboard of Africa, South Africa and KwaZulu-Natal - a province of the highest biodiversity, regarded as the adventure hub of the country with accommodation offerings in the mountains, the bush veld or on the coast.</h2>\r\n<p>Wildside is read by people who love to travel, care about the environment, enjoy outdoor activities like snorkelling, fishing, bird watching, walking, horse riding, abseiling, or just relaxing at a mountain retreat or a quiet bush lodge. \r\nWildside seeks unique travel destinations, exciting adventure, and brings readers seriously great stuff to do for all ages, including families.\r\nThere is always a significant amount of content in Wildside, and often more content than in other magazines in this genre. </p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="tab-pane" id="Readers">\r\n<h2>Eco-minded destination based travellers seeking  accommodation, specific outdoor activities, stimulating adventure, who have in interest in conservation, culture and history.</h2>\r\n      <h4>One remarkable feature is that Wildside has up to a 12 month shelf life in reserves, lodges and doctors rooms and in some instances has a readership of over 15 people per magazine.</h4>\r\n\r\n<p><table class="table table-condensed">\r\n<tr>\r\n<td >Game reserve visitors<br />\r\nConservation minded traveller<br />\r\nLeading conservation organisations and corporates<br />\r\nMountain and bush trailists<br />\r\nMountain bikers<br />\r\nBirdwatchers</td>\r\n<td>Scuba Divers<br />\r\nHorse riders<br />\r\nWhale watchers<br />\r\nSaltwater and Fly Fishermen<br />\r\nKayakers and canoeists<br />\r\nWeekend meanderers</td>\r\n<td >Beach and marine enthusiasts<br />\r\nCaravan and Campers<br />\r\nOverlanders<br />\r\nExplorers<br />\r\nPhotographers<br />\r\nSpa and wellness</td>\r\n </tr>\r\n</table></p>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class="tab-pane" id="Facts">\r\n<h2>Fast Facts</h2>\r\n        <table width="550" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n          <tr>\r\n            <td width="114"><p><strong>Frequency</strong></p></td>\r\n            <td width="436">Quarterly</td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n          <tr>\r\n            <td><p><strong>Contents</strong></p></td>\r\n            <td>Ecotravel - Outdoor Adventure - Conservation</td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n          <tr>\r\n            <td valign="top"><p><strong>Distribution</strong></p></td>\r\n            <td>South African retail outlets CNA, Exlusive Books and SPAR group<br/>\r\n              7 500 Gold Rhino Club subscribers<br/>\r\n              500 Wildlands Conservation Trust subscribers<br/>\r\n              Camps and Reserves in KZN <br/>\r\n              National and International subscriptions<br/>\r\n              Tour Operators (winter)<br/>\r\n              Selected Lodges, Hotels and Reserves (Spring)<br/>\r\n              Doctors Rooms in Gauteng<br/>\r\n              </td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n          <tr>\r\n            <td><p><strong>Readership</strong></p></td>\r\n            <td>100 000 National &amp; International </td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n          <tr>\r\n            <td><p><strong>Retail Price</strong></p></td>\r\n            <td>R24.95</td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n          <tr>\r\n            <td><p ><strong>Print Run</strong></p></td>\r\n            <td>17 500</td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n          <tr>\r\n            <td><p><strong>Demographics</strong></p></td>\r\n            <td>LSM 7-10</td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </table>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n <div class="tab-pane" id="Rate">\r\n<table width="566" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1">\r\n          <tr>\r\n            <td height="30" colspan="8"><h2>Main Body</h2></td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n          <tr>\r\n            <td width="10">&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td width="222" height="27"><strong>ADVERT TYPE</strong></td>\r\n            <td width="55" height="27"><strong>WIDTH</strong></td>\r\n            <td width="14">&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td width="71" height="27"><strong>HEIGHT</strong></td>\r\n            <td width="182" height="27"><strong>COST EX VAT</span></strong></td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n          <tr>\r\n            <td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td height="20">Double Page Spread</td>\r\n            <td height="20">420mm</td>\r\n            <td>x</td>\r\n            <td height="20">285mm</td>\r\n            <td> R 33 000</td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n          <tr>\r\n            <td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td height="20">Inside Front Cover</td>\r\n            <td height="20">210mm</td>\r\n            <td>x</td>\r\n            <td height="20">285mm</td>\r\n            <td> R 25 000</td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n          <tr>\r\n            <td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td height="20">Back Cover</td>\r\n            <td height="20">210mm</td>\r\n            <td>x</td>\r\n            <td height="20">285mm</td>\r\n            <td> R 25 000</td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n          <tr>\r\n            <td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td height="20">Full Page</td>\r\n            <td height="20">210mm</td>\r\n            <td>x</td>\r\n            <td height="20">285mm</td>\r\n            <td> R 20 000</td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n          <tr>\r\n            <td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td height="20">Half Page</td>\r\n            <td height="20">190mm</td>\r\n            <td>x</td>\r\n            <td height="20">130mm</td>\r\n            <td> R 10 000</td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n          <tr>\r\n            <td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td height="20">Third Page Horizontal</td>\r\n            <td height="20">190mm</td>\r\n            <td>x</td>\r\n            <td height="20">85mm</td>\r\n            <td> R 7 125</td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n          <tr>\r\n            <td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td height="20">Third Page Vertical</td>\r\n            <td height="20">61mm</td>\r\n            <td>x</td>\r\n            <td height="20">265mm</td>\r\n            <td> R 7 125</td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n          <tr>\r\n            <td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td height="20">Quarter Page</td>\r\n            <td height="20">92mm</td>\r\n            <td>x</td>\r\n            <td height="20">130mm</td>\r\n            <td> R 5 400</td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n          <tr>\r\n            <td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td height="20">Eighth Page</td>\r\n            <td height="20">92mm</td>\r\n            <td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n            <td height="20">63mm</td>\r\n            <td> R 2 400</td>\r\n          </tr>\r\n        </table>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class="tab-pane" id="Distribution">\r\n<h2>Wildside has a finely targeted and niche distribution to a discerning readership estimated at 100 000</h2>\r\n        <h4>Wildside is a subscription based publication sent to the Golden Rhino Club members and is also sold at retail outlets nationwide including Spar Group, CNA, Exclusive Books, Airports and a free distribution to Doctors Rooms in Gauteng.</h4>\r\n<dl class="dl-horizontal"><dt><strong>Gold Card Subscribers</strong></dt>\r\n         <dd> 7 500 - Exclusively and directly to more than 7 500 paying Rhino Gold members<br/>\r\n          <dt><strong>Wildlands Subscribers</strong></dt>\r\n         <dd> 500 - Wildlands Conservation Trust distributes to its selected corporate donors and a growing database of entrants of Wild Series MTB events.\r\n          <dt><strong>Game Reserves</strong></dt>\r\n          <dd> 2 500 National and international tourists at the bedside of top KZN camps and reserves</dd>\r\n          <dt><strong>National Distribution</strong></dt>\r\n          <dd>6000 are distributed nationally through retail outlets includeing doctors rooms in Gauteng</dd>\r\n          <dt><strong>Indaba Edition </strong></dt>\r\n         <dd>1000 are distributed throughout Africa''s largest Travel Trade show</dd>\r\n          <dt><strong>Travel Operators</strong></dt>\r\n         <dd>450 are distributed to  top travel operators locally and internationally for the Winter edition</dd>\r\n          <dt><strong>Lodges & Hotels</strong></dt>\r\n          <dd>650 are distributed to a bespoke list of South Africa''s top Lodges, Hotels and Game Reserves during the Spring Edition</dd>\r\n          <dt><strong>General</strong></dt> \r\n          <dd>Outdoor enthusiasts &amp; adventure seekers, Tourists, travellers and Wildside Warrior Subscribers</dd>\r\n</dl>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class="tab-pane" id="Booking">\r\n <h2>WILDSIDE MAGAZINE - Booking Deadlines</h2>\r\n <p> \r\n<strong>AUTUMN/Indaba EDITION <br/>April 2013<br/></strong>\r\nThis is the annual Indaba edition, widely distributed at the Indaba from the successful Wildside stand and to tour operators and visitors.<br/>\r\nBooking deadline: 19 March 2013<br/>\r\nMaterial deadline: 26 March 2013<br/>\r\nOn sale nationwide: 22 April 2013</p>\r\n\r\n <p> \r\n<strong>WINTER EDITION <br/>June 2013<br/></strong>\r\nThe features in this snug edition include the uKhahlamba Drakensberg, the Midlands, and a feature on fun weekends.<br/>\r\nBooking deadline: 25 May 2013<br/>\r\nMaterial deadline: 1 June 2013<br/>\r\nOn sale nationwide: 2 July 2013</p>\r\n\r\n<p> \r\n<strong>SPRING EDITION<br/>\r\nSeptember 2013<br/></strong>\r\nAffordable family destinations will be featured, along with the well established spa feature.<br/>\r\nBooking deadline: 6 August 2013<br/>\r\nMaterial deadline: 13 August 2013<br/>\r\nOn sale nationwide: 17 September 2013</p>\r\n\r\n<p> \r\n<strong>SUMMER EDITION<br/>\r\nDecember 2013<br/></strong>\r\nThe big fat fabulous holiday edition including two features – Quick Escapes - places within 1.5 hrs of city centres; \r\nEastern Cape great places and top game reserves.<br/>\r\nBooking deadline: 5 November 2013<br/>\r\nMaterial deadline: 12 November 2013<br/>\r\nOn sale nationwide: 10 December 2013</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>', '', '', '2012-10-10 14:46:00', '2012-10-10 14:46:00', '', 'full'),
(43, 'No', 'No', 'Competitions', 0, '', 'Shaping Kruger - enter now for a chance to win one of five books', 'Shaping_Kruger.jpg', '', '', 'The Kruger National Park is one of the world’s leading stewards of biological diversity. Its management requires ongoing monitoring and re-evaluation to ensure that species survive. Shaping Kruger provides fascinating insight into the lives, habits and behaviour of the larger animals that significantly affect the workings of the park. ', 'It expertly synthesizes decades of ground-breaking research into the animals and their environment, examining along the way individual species; predator-prey relationships; mammal distribution, and browsing and grazing interactions. \r\n<br/><br/>\r\nThis detailed look at how Park management has had to interpret, monitor and adapt the processes that allow species to survive – even thrive – in an ever-changing environment makes for an intriguing and enlightening read. Mitch Reardon is a wildlife photographer and writer. He is the author and photographer of five books.', '', '', '2012-10-11 04:29:00', '2012-10-11 04:30:00', 'Shaping Kruger: The dynamics of managing wildlife in Africa’s premier game park by Mitch Reardon\r\n\r\n<span style="color:red;">Question: Who wrote this book?</span>', ''),
(44, 'yes', 'No', 'Wildside-Warriors', 0, '', 'PROJECT RHINO KZN founding member organisations', 'wsprojectrhino.jpg', '', '', 'Project Rhino KZN is made up of legitimate, expert organisations with a common vision and goal. It identifies synergies through an integrated approach, and is a representative body that carries powerful leverage ability, aimed at eliminating rhino poaching and securing the rhino populations in KZN. ', '<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd">\r\n<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">\r\n<head>\r\n<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8" />\r\n<title>Untitled Document</title>\r\n</head>\r\n\r\n<body>\r\n</body>\r\n</html>\r\n\r\nThe association''s members work together on the following critically needed interventions including increased intelligence and surveillance, increased field ranger competence, improving legal ability, increased communication sharing, public awareness and education.\r\n<br/><br/>\r\n<strong>All donations collected for PROJECT RHINO KZN are administrated by the AFRICAN CONSERVATION TRUST on behalf of the founding members.</strong>\r\n\r\n<br/><br/>\r\n<section class="indexclear">\r\n<img src="http://www.wildsidesa.co.za/admin/upload/server/php/files/ACT.jpg" width="100" height="137" id="indeximage"> \r\n<h3>African Conservation Trust (ACT)</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>ACT is dedicated to preserving Africa''s wildlife and environmental heritage and acts as a resource to Project Rhino members who are actively engaged in rhino conservation and anti-poaching.  A key goal for 2012 is to raise R10million to fund tangible and urgently needed interventions, which will collectively strengthen efforts to counteract rhino poaching. <br/> \r\n  <br/>    \r\n      <br/><strong> Contact: </strong>	Sheelagh Antrobus\r\n      <br/><strong> Tel: </strong>	033-342 2844\r\n      <br/><strong> Email: </strong><a href="mailto:funding@projectafrica.com">funding@projectafrica.com</a><a href="#"></a><br/><strong> Website: </strong><a href="http://www.projectafrica.com">www.projectafrica.com</a></p>\r\n</section>  \r\n   \r\n<section class="indexclear">\r\n<img src="http://www.wildsidesa.co.za/admin/upload/server/php/files/Space-for-Elephants-Thanda-Foundation.jpg" width="200" height="53" id="indeximage">      \r\n      <h3>Thanda Foundation</h3>\r\n     <p> The Thanda Foundation is dedicated to educating and informing communities bordering the Thanda Private Game Reserve of the need to protect the wildlife legacy and biodiversity of northern KwaZulu-Natal.  In recognition of the dire situation of the rhino, Thanda is one of the founding members of Project Rhino KZN and is actively involved in its conservation efforts. <br/> <br/> \r\n      \r\n      <br/><strong> Contact: </strong>	Dulcie Oliver\r\n     <br/> <strong> Tel: </strong>	035 5731899\r\n      <br/><strong> Email: </strong>		<a href="mailto:funding@projectafrica.com">funding@projectafrica.com</a>\r\n     <br/> <strong> Website: </strong>	 <a href="http://www.thanda.com">www.thanda.com</a></p>\r\n     <h3>Space for Elephants Foundation</h3> \r\n      <p>We see the survival of our rhino and all wildlife in Africa like the African 3 legged pot that provides food: if one leg collapses, we will go hungry.    Space for Elephants Foundation rhino work includes: Protecting Rhinos in the field;Working with communities, educating them on the value of rhino to South Africa and intelligence and information gathering.<br/>\r\n      \r\n      <br/><strong> Contact: </strong>	Digs Pascoe\r\n      <br/><strong> Email: </strong>		<a href="mailto:funding@projectafrica.com">funding@projectafrica.com</a>\r\n      <br/><strong> Tel: </strong>	082 9262571 or  035 4745181\r\n      <br/><strong> Website: </strong>	<a href="http://www.space4elephants.org">www.space4elephants.org</a></p>  \r\n      \r\n</section>     \r\n<section class="indexclear">\r\n <img src="http://www.wildsidesa.co.za/admin/upload/server/php/files/KZN-Wildlife-Logo.jpg" width="100" height="121" id="indeximage">\r\n<h3> Ezemvelo KZN Wildlife</h3>\r\n      \r\n     <p> Ezemvelo KZN Wildlife is entrusted with the long-term conservation of the regions rich biodiversity for the people of South Africa and their vision is to ensure effective conservation and sustainable use of KwaZulu Natal''s biodiversity in collaboration with stakeholders for the benefit of present and future generations. EKZNW is involved in numerous anti-poaching initiatives; visit website for details.<br/> <br/> \r\n     \r\n      <br/><strong> Website: </strong>	<a href="http://www.kznwildlife.com">www.kznwildlife.com</a>\r\n      <br/><strong> Tel: </strong>	033 845 1999</p>  \r\n      \r\n</section>     \r\n<section class="indexclear">\r\n <img src="http://www.wildsidesa.co.za/admin/upload/server/php/files/wildlands.jpg" width="130" height="122" id="indeximage">      \r\n     <h3> Wildlands Conservation Trust</h3>\r\n      <p>The Wildlands Conservation Trust''s Rhino Conservation Project aims to preserve rhino populations in KwaZulu-Natal by employing advanced surveillance technologies to improve monitoring and security.<br/> <br/> \r\n     \r\n      <br/><strong> Contact: </strong>	Kevin McCann, Strategic Manager - Stewardship, \r\n      <br/>Tel: 		033 343 6380 or 083 447 0657      \r\n      <br/><strong> Email: </strong>		<a href="mailto:funding@projectafrica.com">funding@projectafrica.com</a>\r\n      <br/><strong> Website: </strong>	<a href="http://www.wildlands.co.za">www.wildlands.co.za</a> </p>  \r\n</section>     \r\n<section class="indexclear"> \r\n\r\n <img src="http://www.wildsidesa.co.za/admin/upload/server/php/files/Wildlife-Act-Fund-logo-CMYK-HOLDING.jpg" width="120" height="141" id="indeximage">      \r\n     <h3> Wildlife ACT Fund</h3>\r\n     <p> The Wildlife ACT Fund supports rhino monitoring projects in KZN and on WWF - Black Rhino Range Expansion sites.  We also currently manage the rhino monitoring work on Somkhanda Game Reserve, and assist with monitoring efforts on Thanda, Tembe, Mkhuze and Hluhluwe-iMfolozi game reserves. <br/> <br/> \r\n     \r\n      <br/><strong> Contact: </strong> 	Simon Morgan   \r\n      <br/><strong> Tel: </strong>	082-0938345\r\n      <br/><strong> Email: </strong>		<a href="mailto:funding@projectafrica.com">funding@projectafrica.com</a>  \r\n     <br/> <strong> Website: </strong> 	<a href="http://www.wildlifeactfund.org">www.wildlifeactfund.org</a> </p>  \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</section>     \r\n<section class="indexclear">      \r\n  <img src="http://www.wildsidesa.co.za/admin/upload/server/php/files/ZWSI-logo.jpg" width="300" height="33">     \r\n     <h3> Zululand Wildlife Security Initiative</h3>\r\n      <p>The Zululand Wildlife Security Initiative (ZWSI) was formed to create joint platform for field ranger training and sharing of information and resources and to assist smaller landowners who aren''t able to fund dedicated anti-poaching units access the skills training needed to protect Zululand''s wildlife.<br/> <br/> \r\n     \r\n      <br/><strong> Contact: </strong> 	Dylan Holmes\r\n      <br/><strong> Tel: </strong>	082-803 1026\r\n      <br/><strong> Email: </strong>		<a href="mailto:funding@projectafrica.com">funding@projectafrica.com</a></p>  \r\n      \r\n </section>     \r\n<section class="indexclear">     \r\n <img src="http://www.wildsidesa.co.za/admin/upload/server/php/files/MNF-Logo.jpg" width="150" height="75" id="indeximage">   \r\n      <h3>Magqubu Ntombela Foundation</h3>\r\n      <p>Dr Ian Player''s Magqubu Ntombela Foundation has established a team of legal, intelligence gathering and forensic experts whose primary aim is to provide support to Ezemvelo KZN Wildlife and the SAPS in their efforts to combat Rhino poaching.  They also provide advice and support to other members of Project Rhino KZN.<br/> <br/> \r\n     \r\n      <br/><strong> Contact: </strong> 	Chris van Heerden   \r\n      <br/> <strong> Tel: </strong>	031-202 8700\r\n      <br/>Cell:		082-454 9441\r\n      <br/><strong> Email: </strong>		<a href="mailto:funding@projectafrica.com">funding@projectafrica.com</a> \r\n      <br/> <strong> Website: </strong> 	<a href="http://www.mnf.org.za">www.mnf.org.za</a></p>  \r\n      \r\n  </section>     \r\n<section class="indexclear">    \r\n  <img src="http://www.wildsidesa.co.za/admin/upload/server/php/files/brrep-logo.jpg" width="150" height="94" id="indeximage"> \r\n     <h3> Black Rhino Range Expansion Project</h3>\r\n      <p>The Black Rhino Range Expansion Project creates new black rhino breeding populations on large areas of land, and supports rhino security on source populations such as Hluhluwe-iMfolozi Park, Mkhuze and Ithala. Seven new populations have been created since 2004.<br/> <br/> \r\n      \r\n      <br/><strong> Contact: </strong> 	Pam Sherriffs\r\n      <br/>Cell:		083-943 1754\r\n      <br/><strong> Email: </strong>		<a href="mailto:funding@projectafrica.com">funding@projectafrica.com</a> <strong> \r\n      <br/>Website: </strong> 	www.wwf.org.za </p> \r\n\r\n       \r\n  <img src="http://www.wildsidesa.co.za/admin/upload/server/php/files/WESSA1.jpg" width="185" height="150" id="indeximage">      \r\n     <h3> WESSA</h3>\r\n     <p> WESSA is involved in fundraising to fund its direct anti-poaching interventions aimed at reducing and preventing rhino poaching. These include poaching information-gathering, the national rhino DNA database development and implementing critically-needed training for field rangers and conservation managers.<br/> <br/> \r\n    \r\n      <br/><strong> Contact: </strong> 	Chris Galliers\r\n      <br/><strong> Tel: </strong>	033-330 3931\r\n      <br/>Cell:		079-504 4296\r\n      <br/> <strong> Email: </strong>		<a href="mailto:funding@projectafrica.com">funding@projectafrica.com</a>\r\n      <br/> <strong> Website: </strong> 	<a href="http://www.wessa.org.za">www.wessa.org.za</a></p>  \r\n      \r\n</section>     \r\n<section class="indexclear"> \r\n  <img src="http://www.wildsidesa.co.za/admin/upload/server/php/files/WAG-logo.jpg" width="125" height="104" id="indeximage">    \r\n     <h3> Wilderness Action Group</h3>\r\n     <p> African rhinos are iconic and wilderness-dependent species.  The Wilderness Action Group is committed to ensuring that South Africa''s wilderness areas are protected and effectively managed for the long-term survival of our rhinos for the benefit of current and future generations<br/>\r\n        <br/>  \r\n      <br/><strong> Contact: </strong> 	Drummond Densham\r\n      <br/><br/><strong> Tel: </strong>	033-330 4039\r\n      <br/>Cell:		083-321 7959\r\n      <br/><strong> Email: </strong>		<a href="mailto:funding@projectafrica.com">funding@projectafrica.com</a>\r\n      <br/> <strong> Website: </strong> 	<a href="http://www.wilderness.org.za">www.wilderness.org.za</a> </p>  \r\n      \r\n</section>     \r\n<section class="indexclear">\r\n \r\n<img src="http://www.wildsidesa.co.za/admin/upload/server/php/files/Game-Ranges-Ass-of-SA.jpg" width="100" height="145" id="indeximage">      \r\n      <h3>Game Rangers Association of SA</h3>\r\n      <p>The Game Rangers Association of Africa is training field rangers in the field, and through the South African Wildlife College and through partnerships, it aims to standardise skills development in the profession.  It also facilitates the management of rhino poaching information.  <br/>\r\n      <br/>  \r\n      <br/><strong> Contact: </strong> 	Chris Galliers\r\n     <br/> Cell:		079-504 4296\r\n      <br/><strong> Email: </strong>		<a href="mailto:funding@projectafrica.com">funding@projectafrica.com</a>\r\n     <br/> <strong> Website: </strong> 	<a href="http://www.gameranger.org">www.gameranger.org</a></p>  \r\n     \r\n     </section>\r\n', '', '', '2012-10-11 05:03:00', '2012-10-11 05:03:00', '', 'full'),
(45, 'No', 'No', 'Competitions', 1, 'Rod MacLeod', 'Win a long weekend at umThiba private lodge for 6 people', 'umThiba.jpg', '', '', 'umThiba private lodge is situated in Kuleni Game Park, a natural sand forest adjacent to Phinda Game Reserve.', 'umThiba is a private lodge set in the heart of Kuleni Game Park, a natural sand forest adjacent to Phinda Game Reserve, in close proximity to St Lucia World Heritage site and is a child friendly establishment offering you wonderful family holidays.\r\n<br/><br/>\r\n\r\nThis comfortable lodge allows the visitor the opportunity to experience nature and wildlife from a deck chair on the veranda or while walking the many nature trails that traverse the diverse indigenous bush and grasslands that make up the park.\r\n<br/><br/>\r\n\r\numThiba is fully equipped for self-catering and is suitable for couples as well as groups of family and friends. All bedrooms are air-conditioned and the accommodation is made up of two en suite bedrooms opening onto decked verandas, with showers under the stars, a one bedroom loft suitable for children and a separate fully equipped selfcontained cottage for two.\r\n<br/><br/>\r\n\r\nHere at umThiba you will find a fully equipped kitchen, an open plan large dining room, kitchen and lounge, spacious open veranda, DSTV, boma with fire pit, and swimming pool. This lodge is fully serviced and there is undercover garaging for 2 cars. This is a great child friendly lodge, close to numerous attractions including the renowned Big Five Game parks, exciting excursions can be arranged to these reserves as well as to Sodwana Bay for diving on magnificent coral reefs, while there is also Lake Sibaya and Lake St Lucia.', '', '', '2013-05-08 18:27:00', '2013-05-08 18:27:00', 'Question: What is the name of the Game Park that umThiba is in?', ''),
(46, 'No', 'No', 'Competitions', 3, 'Rod MacLeod', 'Thula Thula Private Game Reserve Competition', 'Thula Thula luxury tent.pdf.jpg', '', '', 'Win a weekend for 2 people for 2 nights at Thula Thula Game Reserve in their luxury tented camp.', 'This malaria-free reserve is known throughout the world because of the late Lawrence Anthony, author of\r\nThe Elephant Whisperer. \r\n\r\nThula Thula is home to elephant, buffalo, rhino, leopard and spectacular birdlife.\r\n\r\nWith its unique atmosphere, stylish décor and superb cuisine, Thula Thula offers you the choice of exclusive accommodation between the Elephant Safari Lodge, a renowned gourmet destination, and the luxury tented camp, offering an authentic and stylish bush experience.', '', '', '2013-05-09 08:55:00', '2013-05-09 08:55:00', 'What animals can be seen from inside the tent in the photograph?', ''),
(47, 'No', 'No', 'Competitions', 0, 'Rod MacLeod', 'ON TRACK – Book competition', 'On-Track-cover.jpg', '', '', 'New from Struik Nature, On Track: Quick ID Guide to Southern and East African Animal Tracks', 'A simple key on the inside front cover directs users to any of 11 categories, such as “cloven hooves”, “paws” or “tramline-like trails”. Nearly 100 animals or closely related groups of animals are depicted; for each, there is a silhouette of front and back feet and a colour photograph of the track; the average measurements for each track; a short description of the track; and information about the circumstances and likely habitat.<br/><br/>\r\n\r\nConcise and to-the-point, this pocket-sized reference will prove indispensable in the field, no matter the experience of the user. <br/><br/>\r\n\r\n<span class="bold">About the authors</span><br/>\r\n\r\nFounders of the African-Arabian Wildlife Research Centre, Chris and Mathilde Stuart, field ecologist and medical doctor respectively, work in the fields of biodiversity surveying and research, photography and film-making. The are well known for their popular science books, and have contributed widely to scientific journals and magazines', '', '', '2013-05-09 15:40:00', '2013-05-09 15:40:00', 'Which organisation are the Authors founding members?', ''),
(48, 'yes', 'yes', 'News', 0, 'Wildlands Conservation Trust', 'New Vulture Hide opens in the uKhahlamba Drakensberg Park at Cathedral Peak', 'young-bearded-vulture_1.jpg', '', '', '“Bearded Vultures are critically endangered with approximately 330 in Southern Africa and only 3000 Cape Vultures,” commented Sonja Krueger of Ezemvelo KZN Wildlife. “These extremely low numbers are mainly as a result of a lack of suitable habitat and food, as well as significant impacts through poisonings and collisions or electrocutions with powerlines,” said Krueger.', 'It is for this reason that the N3 Toll Concession (N3TC) has generously donated funds in order to construct a hide at Cathedral Peak in the uKhahlamba Drakensberg Park, a world heritage site in KZN. By constructing a hide and a feeding site in this Park, it is hoped that the vulture populations of the area will have a much more stable source of food.\r\n<br/><br/>\r\n\r\nThe hide came about through collaboration between the N3TC, Ezemvelo KZN Wildlife and Wildlands Conservation Trust and is one of three which are to be built within the Drakensberg area. Designed by Ezemvelo KZN Wildlife’s Glenn Harboth and superbly built by Lawrie Raubenheimer (Heritage Design and Creations cc), this hide has been modelled on the local rocks and blends in beautifully to its surrounds. The N3TC has a 30 year contract to manage and maintain the N3 highway and, as a result, they bring a large number of people into the area. “It is important for us to leave a legacy behind when we one day step out of this area,” said Neil Tolmie, CEO of N3TC. “It was for this reason that we easily agreed to support the conservation of the Bearded and other vultures within the area three years ago and we look forward to building on our relationship with Wildlands and KZN Wildlife in the years to come.”\r\n<br/><br/>\r\n\r\nSaturday the 7th September, only 2 days after the official launch, it was International Vulture Awareness Day, and we hope facilities such as the hide launched at Cathedral Peak will add to this awareness.\r\n<br/><br/>\r\n\r\nThe hide will be able to accommodate a number of visitors at a time and is fitted with rain water harvesting tanks and full ablutions. “This is an amazing project which will not only create an additional feeding site for these endangered birds, but also much needed awareness amongst the public, allowing them the privilege of spending time close to the action of feeding vultures,” said Kevin McCann, Strategic Manager of Wildlands. “Without the incredible support of the N3TC and passion of the staff at KZN Wildlife, this project would not have been possible,” McCann concluded.', '', '', '2013-09-13 14:01:00', '2013-09-13 14:01:00', 'Juvenile Bearded Vulture - photo by Sonja Krueger', ''),
(49, 'No', 'No', 'Competitions', 1, '', 'Win 1 of 5 Copies – THE FIRST AID GUIDE TO SPIDER BITES AND SCORPION STINGS', 'z_first_aid.jpg', '', '', 'THE FIRST AID GUIDE TO SPIDER BITES AND SCORPION STINGS', 'Five readers stand the chance to win a copy of First Aid Guide to Spider Bites and Scorpion Stings by Jonathan Leeming, author of\r\nScorpions of Southern Africa. This self-published book has been written for the general public and contains comprehensive\r\nand up-to-date information, including how to identify southern Africa’s medically important spiders and scorpions and what first\r\naid treatment is applicable in particular situations.', '', '', '2013-09-01 08:19:00', '2013-09-02 08:19:00', 'What is the name of another book authored by Jonathan Leeming?', ''),
(50, 'No', 'No', 'Competitions', 0, '', 'Win a midweek 2 night breakaway for 4 (family sharing) to De Hoop Nature Resrve', 'z_dehoop.jpg', '', '', 'Win a midweek 2 night breakaway for 4 (family sharing) in a self-catering De Hoop Collection Cottage i the heart of the De Hoop Nayure Reserve.', 'De Hoop Nature Reserve – just three hours’ drive from Cape Town – is an unspoilt wilderness area leading down to an untouched\r\ncoastline. The De Hoop Collection is set amidst this breathtaking natural scenery with its highly productive ecosystem. A bird\r\nlover’s paradise, the reserve is home to some 260 bird species and each year, pelicans come to breed on the vlei waters.\r\n\r\nThe three nautical miles of De Hoop Marine Reserve beyond the shoreline offer some of the best whale viewing in the world, with some 40% of the global southern right whale population coming to the bay each year to breed. Every year, between June and early December, the bay teems with cows and their calves. At other times of the year, pods of dolphins enthrall visitors. \r\n\r\nDe Hoop is ideal for a fun relaxed family getaway, offering a variety of activities and facilities. A wide range of accommodation types is artistically incorporated with historical buildings, creating a village-type atmosphere, where guests can choose to socialise or enjoy privacy.', '', '', '2013-09-01 08:35:00', '2013-09-02 08:35:00', 'Question: How many hours drive from Cape Town is De Hoop Nature Reserve?', ''),
(51, 'No', 'No', 'Competitions', 0, '', 'WIN A WHALE WATCHING TRIP AND A HIPPO AND CROC CRUISE', 'z_whales.jpg', '', '', 'Win a boat-based whale watching trip and a “hippo and croc” boat cruise for four people with Advantage Tours and Charters', 'Win a boat-based whale watching trip and a “hippo and croc” boat cruise for four people with Advantage Tours and Charters, valued at R1 800.00. Situated on KwaZulu-Natal’s north coast at St Lucia, Advantage Tours and Charters, established in 1991, will take you to see those gentle giants of the ocean, the humpback whales, aboard their large hard-hulled vessel.\r\n\r\nExperienced skippers do a beach surf launch and take you out to sea for this experience of a lifetime and provide interesting information about these mighty creatures as you view them – you may even see them breeching. The whales migrate past this stretch of coastline between June to November, to calve and breed in the warm waters of the Indian Ocean, moving as far as Mozambique and Madagascar before making the journey back to the Antarctic.\r\n\r\nThe prize also includes a boat-based cruise along the St Lucia Estuary to view hippos, crocs and birdlife.', '', '', '2013-09-01 08:49:00', '2013-09-02 08:49:00', 'Question: Which company conducts the Whale Watching Tours in St Lucia?', ''),
